  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Cut your white cabbage and carrots in half. Then, using a mandolin if you have one or knife if you don’t, slice your white cabbage, carrots, and radishes into thin slices."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Lay your radishes on top of each other and cut into matchsticks. Repeat this step with the carrots."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Put your chopped carrots and radishes in a bowl with the juice of a lime. Add salt and mayonnaise and stir well. Set aside in the fridge while you prepare the rest."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Now it’s time to coat your prawns. Mix your panko breadcrumbs with chilli flakes on a plate. Add a layer of mayonnaise on another."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Dip the prawns into the mayo and then into the panko mixture until they are all fully coated"
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Drizzle with a little oil then put into the air fryer at 200°C for 8 mins."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "While your prawns cook, make your firecracker sauce. Grab a small bowl and grate in the garlic and ginger. Then add the buffalo sauce, soy, and rice vinegar."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Once your prawns are crispy and golden, it’s time to assemble the bánh mì. Add a layer of mayonnaise on the inside of the baguette then top it with the slaw, prawns, sauce, and a generous helping of coriander."
    }
  ],
